 444:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/misc.c ****             // Compatability Errata:
 445:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/misc.c ****             //  Some systems try to hide drive space with thier INT 13h driver
 446:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/misc.c ****             //  This does not hide space from the OS driver. This means the MBR
 447:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/misc.c ****             //  that gets created from DOS is smaller than the MBR created from
 448:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/misc.c ****             //  a real OS (NT & Win98). This leads to BlkIo->LastBlock being
